AN ACT relating to governmental administration; revising
provisions governing the submission of certain reports by
the State Land Registrar; repealing provisions requiring
the State Forester Firewarden to submit an annual report
relating to the Lake Tahoe Basin; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the State Land Registrar to report quarterly to the State
2 Board of Examiners regarding certain real property or interests in real property
3 transferred in the Lake Tahoe Basin. (NRS 321.5954) Section 1 of this bill instead
4 requires the State Land Registrar to report annually to the Board.
5 Existing law requires the State Forester Firewarden to submit an annual report
6 concerning fire prevention and forest health in the Nevada portion of the Lake
7 Tahoe Basin to certain governmental entities. (NRS 528.150) Section 2 of this bill
8 repeals this requirement.
